Package com.deadmandungeons.audioconnect

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AudioConnectClient.PlayerAudioDataWriter  
    AudioConnectConfig  
    PlayerScheduler.PlayerDataWriter
    The interface defining basic player data processing methods to be executed by a PlayerScheduler
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioConnect
    The main plugin class.
    The instance of this class can be obtained by AudioConnect.getInstance()
    AudioConnectClient
    The class which operates as the data supplier client to an AudioConnect server.
    Note: this class and its operations are thread safe.
    AudioConnectClient.PlayerConnection  
    AudioConnectConfig.AudioTrackSettings  
    AudioList
    A simple wrapper to a collection containing all available audio IDs for the configured account.
    The operations in this class will only be useful if the client is connected.
    PlayerAudioStatusEvent
    Called when the connection status for a player between the web client, Minecraft client, and the AudioConnect server changes.
    PlayerScheduler
    This class facilitates the scheduled execution of a repeated data processing task for a set of players in an efficient manner through load balancing.
    Players added to this scheduler are partitioned into separate tasks which are executed at different times (or ticks) displaced from each other as a means to balance the load.
